cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is about improving word sense disambiguation using pre-trained contextualized word representations. The paper focuses on natural language processing tasks, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. The use of pre-trained models also suggests that it could belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Additionally, the paper explores different strategies for integrating pre-trained models, which could fall under the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The use of benchmark datasets suggests that it could also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with language ambiguity, which could also fall under the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category.
